  "prompt": "Which raw materials are needed for photosynthesis?",
  "response": "Photosynthesis primarily requires three raw materials:\n\n1. **Carbon Dioxide (CO\u2082)**: This gas is absorbed from the atmosphere through small openings in plant leaves called stomata.\n2. **Water (H\u2082O)**: Plants take up water from the soil through their roots.\n3. **Light Energy**: Specifically, sunlight is captured by chlorophyll, the green pigment in plant cells, which is crucial for converting light energy into chemical energy.\n\nThese materials are used in the photosynthesis process to produce glucose (C\u2086H\u2081\u2082O\u2086) and oxygen (O\u2082) as byproducts. The overall chemical equation for photosynthesis can be summarized as:\n\n\\[ 6 \\, CO\u2082 + 6 \\, H\u2082O + \\text{light energy} \\rightarrow C\u2086H\u2081\u2082O\u2086 + 6 \\, O\u2082 \\]",
